(42, 15, 28, 23, 66, 5, 5, 'would not go in', 'Rejection and Divine Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejection and the father''s response to anger in both passages. In Luke, the father''s act of coming out to the angry son parallels the Lord''s response to those who are cast out in Isaiah.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
